Four police officers have been arrested over claims of robbery with violence while enforcing the covid 19 pandemic curfew rules&hellip; in what has left the police service on the spot over the implementation of the curfew protocols Kenyans took to the social media calling for the curfew to be lifted under the hashtag end curfew now. However, President Uhuru Kenyatta has once again issued a public order that the country continues to observe the curfew for a further period of 60 days. This came on a day that the high court ruled that the national security advisory committee has no powers to order the police on how to conduct its duties. The court observed that the top security organ was not part of the police service.